00:16:02.062 --> 00:16:08.132
Now, our third economic theory to look at the lottery through is the sunk cost fallacy.

00:16:09.102 --> 00:16:13.742
This is the idea that many people tend to continue to do something because they

00:16:13.742 --> 00:16:18.122
have already spent time or money doing something and they don’t want it to be

00:16:18.432 --> 00:16:23.932
wasted, even though, rationally speaking, they would be better off simply stopping.

00:16:25.442 --> 00:16:31.062
As far as the lottery is concerned, it is a prime example of the sunk cost fallacy.

00:16:32.222 --> 00:16:39.482
