00:16:57.796 --> 00:17:03.006
A person who has spent €10,000 on the lottery and not won a cent will have

00:17:03.006 --> 00:17:06.916
exactly the same probability of winning as someone who has never played.

00:17:07.966 --> 00:17:12.846
Yet the first person will often think that they must win soon, hence

00:17:13.026 --> 00:17:16.816
they keep on buying tickets to try to recoup their earlier losses.

00:17:17.336 --> 00:17:19.896
So, that is the sunk cost fallacy.

